  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nPlease include information like:\r\n\r\nIf one starts trinity with debug logging enabled (`trinity -l debug`) one does really only see debug messages from trinity but not those that are logged via the p2p or evm layer (these layers remain on log level `info`). \r\n\r\nConsidering that trinity is the main user facing software, am I right to assume that we actually do want to see debug messages from p2p/evm if one starts trinity with `-l debug`?",
