    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "So my point about some of the `p2p`namespace stuff needing to be `trinity` namespace stuff should cover the majority of this.  For example, the `p2p.peer.LESPeer` uses the logger `p2p.peer.Peer`.  This should really probably be relocated to be under the `trinity` python module and to use a `trinity.` namespaced logger.\r\n\r\nThis should fix **most** of these, though there may be a few where we *should* explicitly include some `p2p` namespaced logging in the trinity output which we can handle as special cases (like maybe loggers burried deep in the authentication code in the `p2p` module)",
